==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mercuric
<hw>Mer*cu"ric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or derived from, mercury; containing mercury; --
said of those compounds of mercury into which this element enters in its
lowest proportion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mercuric chloride</b></col>, <cd>corrosive sublimate. See
<er>mercury bichloride</er> and <er>Corrosive</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mercurification</ent>⟦br⟧
